1
00:00:10,867 --> 00:00:11,767
<i> Miss Ligaya!</i>

2
00:00:13,733 --> 00:00:14,500
<i> Hello, Ma'am Jade.</i>

3
00:00:14,633 --> 00:00:15,600
<i>I've finally found Miss Ligaya.</i>

4
00:00:15,733 --> 00:00:16,900
<i> She was with a man earlier.</i>

5
00:00:17,033 --> 00:00:19,333
<i>Where is he? I shot him
and left him on the street.</i>

6
00:00:19,467 --> 00:00:20,467
<i> He's your father.</i>

7
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:23,600
<i> You have the same symptoms.</i>

8
00:00:23,733 --> 00:00:25,667
<i> You got that...</i>

9
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:26,567
<i> What did I get?</i>

10
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:27,467
<i> What is it?</i>

11
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:29,733
<i>What you're going through, dear.</i>

12
00:00:29,867 --> 00:00:31,167
<i> I'm not crazy!</i>

13
00:00:31,300 --> 00:00:32,500
<i> Here's to a better...</i>

14
00:00:32,633 --> 00:00:34,533
<i> brighter Artemis.</i>

15
00:00:34,700 --> 00:00:36,833
<i>I had to change myself
to recover</i>

16
00:00:36,967 --> 00:00:39,833
<i> from everything you did to me.</i>

17
00:00:39,967 --> 00:00:41,700
<i>What are you doing in my party?</i>

18
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:42,600
<i> Guard!</i>

19
00:00:42,733 --> 00:00:45,600
<i>Bring this crazy gatecrasher
out.</i>

20
00:00:45,733 --> 00:00:46,800
<i> What?</i>

21
00:00:46,933 --> 00:00:48,267
<i> Why aren't you moving yet?</i>

22
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:51,367
<i>Do you want me to call
the manager of this bar?</i>

23
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:52,667
<i> She's in front of you.</i>

24
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:53,433
<i> Excuse me?</i>

25
00:00:53,567 --> 00:00:55,000
<i> I'm the manager of this bar.</i>

26
00:00:55,133 --> 00:00:57,633
<i>So talk to me if you need
anything.</i>

27
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:34,200
Go on.

28
00:01:34,333 --> 00:01:35,800
I'll take care of her.

29
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:45,567
So, who do you think you are?

30
00:01:47,267 --> 00:01:54,700
No matter what you wear
and even if you put

31
00:01:54,833 --> 00:02:02,000
jewelry all over your body,
it won't change who you are.

32
00:02:02,133 --> 00:02:10,667
You are still Emma,
who's dumb and weak.

33
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:17,133
The person who can't stand
by her family.

34
00:02:18,633 --> 00:02:20,200
Let me remind you.

35
00:02:21,233 --> 00:02:25,633
I can have you dragged
out of here if I want to.

36
00:02:32,633 --> 00:02:34,200
I'm so scared.

37
00:02:35,333 --> 00:02:36,967
You're so feisty.

38
00:02:38,067 --> 00:02:45,633
Or maybe you're bold because
someone's helping you.

39
00:02:45,767 --> 00:02:48,200
Let's just say that God
is with me.

40
00:02:49,467 --> 00:02:51,767
Because he didn't forsake me.

41
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:56,133
He didn't let me rot in the
place where you brought me.

42
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:58,967
So be scared now that I bounced
back.

43
00:03:01,167 --> 00:03:06,833
Because I will take
back everything I lost.

44
00:03:06,967 --> 00:03:09,267
And I will take Mookie
away from you.

45
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:15,067
Good luck, then.

46
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:21,067
That is if they'll come with
you.

47
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,500
As far as I know,

48
00:03:25,033 --> 00:03:27,367
they didn't just forget
about you.

49
00:03:28,533 --> 00:03:32,333
They also harbor anger towards
you.

50
00:03:33,867 --> 00:03:35,067
So, go ahead.

51
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:43,067
Call them, message them, go to
them, for all I care, Emma.

52
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:52,500
But don't cry if they drive you
away as you did to them.

53
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:56,700
Cheers, everyone!

54
00:03:56,833 --> 00:03:59,433
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

55
00:04:22,933 --> 00:04:25,500
Jade, are you okay?

56
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:38,900
I think I made a mistake.

57
00:04:39,967 --> 00:04:43,233
Maybe I shouldn't have told her
that I'd take Mookie back.

58
00:04:43,367 --> 00:04:46,667
What if Jade is paranoid?
What if she hurts Mookie?

59
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:48,133
Don't be afraid.

60
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:51,833
If there's someone who should be
scared about what happened,

61
00:04:53,367 --> 00:04:54,400
it's Jade.

62
00:04:55,833 --> 00:05:03,867
Because you showed her that
you're no longer the Emma

63
00:05:06,667 --> 00:05:08,767
that she can easily trample.

64
00:05:17,133 --> 00:05:18,567
<i> I'm really sorry, Jade.</i>

65
00:05:18,700 --> 00:05:23,333
<i>I would've told you had I known
Emma was the bar manager.</i>

66
00:05:23,467 --> 00:05:26,500
Well, at least we knew
what happened to Emma.

67
00:05:26,633 --> 00:05:29,800
But I can't let her get what she
wants.

68
00:05:29,933 --> 00:05:32,067
She can't take Mookie back.

69
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:35,433
And she can't get near
Mookie and Danilo.

70
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:38,967
<i>Sometimes, it makes me think
you're Olive.</i>

71
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:41,733
<i>There are times that
you talk the same way.</i>

72
00:05:41,867 --> 00:05:44,667
<i>Just like now, it's
giving paranoid vibes.</i>

73
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:47,467
<i>I thought you wanted to
give them closure as a family?</i>

74
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:49,367
Come on, Astrid.

75
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:51,467
You saw what happened,
didn't you?

76
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,667
Emma wasn't in a miserable
condition

77
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:55,500
like what I'd imagined.

78
00:05:55,633 --> 00:05:56,900
Could you imagine?

79
00:05:57,033 --> 00:05:59,433
That witch is now a bar manager.

80
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:01,567
She didn't even return
to her family.

81
00:06:02,667 --> 00:06:06,333
That means she doesn't
deserve closure.

82
00:06:06,467 --> 00:06:09,500
I don't know why that woman had
to come back.

83
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:15,667
Just message me if you're
already dismissed

84
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:17,233
or have to stay longer.

85
00:06:17,367 --> 00:06:19,467
So I'll know if I have
to adjust. Okay?

86
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:20,733
Okay, Aunt Jade.

87
00:06:20,867 --> 00:06:23,133
Get inside so you won't be late.

88
00:06:23,267 --> 00:06:24,467
Don't forget.

89
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:25,800
Don't let anyone mistreat you.

90
00:06:25,933 --> 00:06:27,367
Of course.

91
00:06:27,500 --> 00:06:28,767
- Have fun today!
- Thanks.

92
00:06:28,900 --> 00:06:29,967
See you!

93
00:06:37,833 --> 00:06:39,067
Look at you.

94
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:43,100
You have the nerve
to come here.

95
00:06:44,233 --> 00:06:47,067
You were a scene stealer
in my event the other day.

96
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:49,867
And now you're hovering
around Mookie at school.

97
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:52,400
I have the right to be here.

98
00:06:52,533 --> 00:06:54,067
I came here for my daughter.

99
00:06:55,100 --> 00:06:58,567
The daughter you left
and neglected.

100
00:07:00,733 --> 00:07:03,367
Don't be so confident, Emma.

101
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:07,167
I can call Mookie and make
her choose between us.

102
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:11,167
And no doubt, she'll choose me.

103
00:07:11,300 --> 00:07:11,967
Snake!

104
00:07:13,267 --> 00:07:16,300
You're brave because you
only didn't get Danilo.

105
00:07:16,467 --> 00:07:18,467
You also poisoned Mookie's mind.

106
00:07:19,767 --> 00:07:21,700
But don't be so confident.

107
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:24,700
Once I remove the poison
in Mookie's mind,

108
00:07:24,833 --> 00:07:29,567
I'll make sure she'll be
disgusted by you

109
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:33,233
and drive you away once
she hears everything.

110
00:07:33,367 --> 00:07:35,800
I dare you to do it.

111
00:07:35,933 --> 00:07:38,667
Don't give such empty threats.

112
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:42,700
Don't tell me you'll make
a scene here.

113
00:07:42,833 --> 00:07:47,133
Let me remind you that
you're not a manager here.

114
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:51,567
I can call a guard
to drag you out.

115
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:55,467
Or better yet, I can file a case
against you.

116
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:59,200
Stalking or harassment.

117
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:00,567
You choose.

118
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:03,133
Eenie meenie miney mo.

119
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:23,500
So you won't leave us alone.

120
00:08:23,633 --> 00:08:31,267
Then I'll find a way for Danilo
and Mookie to drive you away.

121
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:57,600
Emma really has a
different effect on you, boss.

122
00:08:59,067 --> 00:09:01,967
Maybe that's why you now rarely
get angry

123
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:03,300
when collecting payments.

124
00:09:04,933 --> 00:09:07,300
Looks like you're serious
with Emma.

125
00:09:08,567 --> 00:09:11,567
I'm planning to confess to Emma.

126
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:15,867
You know, like proposing.

127
00:09:17,133 --> 00:09:21,267
Emma's so busy
with her daughter.

128
00:09:22,333 --> 00:09:24,667
Does she have time to be
in a relationship?

129
00:09:26,267 --> 00:09:27,333
I'm sure she has.

130
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:28,867
Come on.

131
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:32,267
She can't say no because
she's so indebted to me.

132
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:35,500
I took care of her.

133
00:09:35,633 --> 00:09:37,933
I took her in and invested
a lot in her.

134
00:09:39,033 --> 00:09:41,900
She'll be ashamed to reject me.

135
00:09:43,367 --> 00:09:45,500
You really are my idol, boss.

136
00:09:49,533 --> 00:09:51,800
It's time for Emma
and me to be together.

137
00:09:53,333 --> 00:09:54,433
But, of course,

138
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:57,400
she's different from the other
girls I met.

139
00:09:58,433 --> 00:10:03,033
So I should do it slowly.

140
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,867
So that she'll fall in love
with me.

141
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:11,233
Logan.

142
00:10:13,133 --> 00:10:16,600
I need help with the bar's
inventory.

143
00:10:16,733 --> 00:10:20,467
<i>Are you just pretending that you
can't remember Logan Alvarez?</i>

144
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:24,933
<i>The man who helped you escape
the crime syndicate in Japan.</i>

145
00:10:25,067 --> 00:10:26,867
<i> Jade's lover?</i>

146
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,033
<i> He's the one helping Emma?</i>

147
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:31,933
<i> He seems a bad person.</i>

148
00:10:32,967 --> 00:10:35,200
<i> But how did he and Emma meet?</i>

149
00:10:35,367 --> 00:10:37,933
<i> And why is he helping Emma?</i>

150
00:10:38,933 --> 00:10:41,867
<i>Now I know why Emma became
courageous.</i>

151
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:45,167
<i>She has a crazy man
she relies on.</i>

152
00:10:56,767 --> 00:10:57,800
Hello, Bryan.

153
00:10:59,533 --> 00:11:01,700
I need you to investigate
someone.

154
00:11:09,100 --> 00:11:10,600
We'll make an itinerary.

155
00:11:20,967 --> 00:11:22,067
Excuse me.

156
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:23,133
Barbie...

157
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:27,700
- Sorry.
- What happened?

158
00:11:27,833 --> 00:11:29,500
I made a mess.

159
00:11:29,633 --> 00:11:30,633
Barbie!

160
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:33,767
Come.

161
00:11:33,900 --> 00:11:34,900
Be careful.

162
00:11:38,767 --> 00:11:39,433
Come on.

163
00:11:44,133 --> 00:11:45,733
- What happened?
- Sorry.

164
00:11:45,867 --> 00:11:48,767
I started shivering
as if I was nervous.

165
00:11:51,367 --> 00:11:53,233
I even made a mess. I'm sorry.

166
00:11:54,467 --> 00:11:55,633
Is it about Mookie again?

167
00:11:58,433 --> 00:12:00,000
I don't know why I'm nervous.

168
00:12:00,133 --> 00:12:02,367
Maybe something bad is happening
to Mookie.

169
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:04,333
Maybe Jade's doing something
to her.

170
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:09,600
Calm down, okay?

171
00:12:09,733 --> 00:12:12,233
I'm sure nothing will happen
to Mookie.

172
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:17,067
So you better change into nice
clothes.

173
00:12:17,233 --> 00:12:19,533
Some VIP guests will come later.

174
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:22,733
To look beautiful.

175
00:12:24,300 --> 00:12:25,633
Okay?

176
00:12:25,767 --> 00:12:26,567
Come on and smile.

177
00:12:28,367 --> 00:12:29,533
You're okay.

178
00:12:45,700 --> 00:12:46,733
Love!

179
00:12:46,867 --> 00:12:47,700
Love, look!

180
00:12:47,867 --> 00:12:48,867
Hurry up!

181
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,333
Look!

182
00:12:50,467 --> 00:12:52,167
Astrid sent this to me.

183
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:54,900
She saw Emma in a bar.

184
00:12:55,033 --> 00:12:55,833
Look!

185
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:59,000
- Emma?
- Isn't that Emma?

186
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:08,900
<i>Maybe she really is the one
I saw at the Activora party.</i>

187
00:13:11,900 --> 00:13:17,000
Why does it seem that she's
already with someone else?

188
00:13:17,133 --> 00:13:18,133
What?

189
00:13:29,133 --> 00:13:31,200
<i>What the investigator said
is true.</i>

190
00:13:31,433 --> 00:13:32,767
<i>Emma is already with someone
else.</i>

191
00:13:34,100 --> 00:13:35,800
Is it just me, love?

192
00:13:35,933 --> 00:13:38,967
Emma seems different.

193
00:13:39,100 --> 00:13:41,600
Even how she dresses.

194
00:13:41,733 --> 00:13:43,833
It seems like she
became wealthy.

195
00:13:43,967 --> 00:13:48,000
Isn't it because of the man
she's hugging?

196
00:13:48,133 --> 00:13:49,067
Wait.

197
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,300
This isn't true.

198
00:13:51,533 --> 00:13:52,700
This isn't true.

199
00:13:52,833 --> 00:13:59,100
I wonder why we couldn't find
Emma when we looked for her.

200
00:13:59,267 --> 00:14:01,067
Well,

201
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:06,467
it's hard to find someone who
doesn't want to be found.

202
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:09,433
This isn't true!

203
00:14:09,567 --> 00:14:11,200
Love, what are you doing?

204
00:14:11,333 --> 00:14:12,567
What's wrong with you?

205
00:14:15,100 --> 00:14:18,500
I want her to tell me herself
if she has another man.

206
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:22,633
Where's Emma? Where's my wife?

207
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:38,367
A few more steps, Emma.

208
00:14:42,433 --> 00:14:43,767
Okay.

209
00:14:43,900 --> 00:14:44,733
Stay here.

210
00:14:52,967 --> 00:14:54,233
Logan, what's this?

211
00:15:04,867 --> 00:15:06,633
Shall we?

212
00:15:13,967 --> 00:15:14,500
Thank you.

213
00:15:16,633 --> 00:15:17,600
For you.

214
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:20,933
Thank you.

215
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:32,133
Girls.

216
00:15:32,267 --> 00:15:33,333
Food, please.

217
00:15:38,367 --> 00:15:41,000
So, is this okay?

218
00:15:42,567 --> 00:15:49,200
You've been stressed for days
now, especially about Mookie.

219
00:15:49,333 --> 00:15:55,600
So I want us to just have fun
tonight.

220
00:15:58,400 --> 00:16:05,367
I hope you won't think about
anything else, but us.

221
00:16:46,967 --> 00:16:49,367
I told you, Danilo.

222
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:51,133
Emma already has someone else.

223
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:57,300
<i> I said face me!</i>

224
00:17:01,233 --> 00:17:02,000
Dan?

225
00:17:06,633 --> 00:17:08,100
- Danilo!
- Wait.

226
00:17:08,233 --> 00:17:09,200
Dan!

227
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:10,300
Dan!

228
00:17:10,433 --> 00:17:11,700
Emma!

229
00:17:11,833 --> 00:17:12,667
Dan!

230
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:25,633
Dan!

231
00:17:25,767 --> 00:17:27,267
Danilo!

232
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:28,433
Dan, wait!

233
00:17:28,567 --> 00:17:31,833
Emma, give Danilo some space.

234
00:17:31,967 --> 00:17:33,667
Stay out of this.

235
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:35,333
Maybe you purposely brought
him here

236
00:17:35,467 --> 00:17:37,700
to make me look bad in front
of him.

237
00:17:37,833 --> 00:17:38,800
Can you please stop?

238
00:17:38,933 --> 00:17:40,400
Danilo, let's talk first.

239
00:17:40,533 --> 00:17:44,233
Talk? There's nothing left
to talk about, Emma!

240
00:17:44,367 --> 00:17:46,600
What I saw was so clear.

241
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:48,967
You already have someone else!

242
00:17:49,133 --> 00:17:52,567
That's why it's easy for you
to forget me and our daughter.

243
00:18:07,633 --> 00:18:10,533
Emma, how could you do this
to me?

244
00:18:10,667 --> 00:18:12,933
I thought you loved Mookie
and me so much?

245
00:18:13,067 --> 00:18:15,767
Why did you leave us?
Why did you push us away, Emma?

246
00:18:17,367 --> 00:18:18,967
We have been looking for you
for a long time.

247
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:24,367
I prayed for months to find you,
Emma.

248
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:27,067
Because Mookie and I miss you
so much.

249
00:18:29,300 --> 00:18:31,267
We looked for you everywhere.

250
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:33,633
We asked many people,
but no one could help.

251
00:18:35,233 --> 00:18:37,133
I couldn't sleep for days.

252
00:18:38,533 --> 00:18:40,600
Because I didn't want to think
that you were already dead.

253
00:18:42,333 --> 00:18:48,533
And now I see you alive
and happy with someone else!

254
00:18:48,667 --> 00:18:49,533
Why, Emma?

255
00:18:49,667 --> 00:18:52,900
Why?
Why did you go with that man?

256
00:18:53,033 --> 00:18:54,633
Is it because he's wealthy?

257
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:57,667
Is it because he can dress you
in nice clothes like that?

258
00:18:57,800 --> 00:19:00,033
Is that why you went with him?

259
00:19:00,167 --> 00:19:03,233
Dan, can you please be
careful with what you say?

260
00:19:03,367 --> 00:19:05,100
You're throwing hurtful words.

261
00:19:05,233 --> 00:19:07,767
What about you and Jade?

262
00:19:07,900 --> 00:19:10,333
Aren't you in a relationship?

263
00:19:10,467 --> 00:19:15,700
Didn't you live together
and become Mookie's parents?

264
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:16,633
Why?

265
00:19:18,833 --> 00:19:20,300
Did you give in to her?

266
00:19:22,133 --> 00:19:23,867
Is it because she can give you
a mansion?

267
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:28,300
Is it because she can give you
your dream business?

268
00:19:28,467 --> 00:19:31,933
Shouldn't I ask you that, Emma?

269
00:19:32,067 --> 00:19:33,667
Why?

270
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:35,933
Who changed a lot?

271
00:19:36,067 --> 00:19:37,033
Isn't it you?

272
00:19:39,067 --> 00:19:43,800
Maybe you chose to become rich
and do well in life.

273
00:19:43,933 --> 00:19:45,300
What for?

274
00:19:45,433 --> 00:19:48,267
So you can easily forget me
and Mookie.

275
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:49,500
Right?

276
00:19:49,633 --> 00:19:53,200
Because money matters to you!

277
00:19:53,333 --> 00:19:56,367
It's like you sold yourself
to that man!

278
00:20:07,567 --> 00:20:09,100
It was you who gave in to Jade!

279
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:11,233
If you really looked for me,
you shouldn't have stopped!

280
00:20:11,367 --> 00:20:12,800
You shouldn't have given up!

281
00:20:13,467 --> 00:20:15,400
You let Jade fool you!

282
00:20:16,300 --> 00:20:17,133
Really, Emma?

283
00:20:18,167 --> 00:20:20,200
Are you really going to divert
that question to Jade?

284
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:25,400
Can you please not blame Jade
for abandoning your family?

285
00:20:25,533 --> 00:20:27,833
Because she doesn't have
anything to do with that.

286
00:20:27,967 --> 00:20:29,100
She does.

287
00:20:29,233 --> 00:20:32,933
She drove me crazy to keep me
away from you and Mookie.

288
00:20:33,067 --> 00:20:34,267
Believe me.

289
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:36,267
Why would I believe you?
Do you have proof?

290
00:20:36,433 --> 00:20:39,467
I saw her talking to Andrea,
the nurse in Havenwood.

291
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:41,300
Did you hear their conversation?

292
00:20:41,433 --> 00:20:43,500
That they were driving you
crazy?

293
00:20:43,633 --> 00:20:44,967
Did you hear them?

294
00:20:45,100 --> 00:20:46,133
No, but...

295
00:20:46,267 --> 00:20:47,133
But what?

296
00:20:47,267 --> 00:20:49,267
You're just making up stories.

297
00:20:50,367 --> 00:20:52,500
Because you were already
mentally ill

298
00:20:52,633 --> 00:20:54,367
when we brought you
to Havenwood,

299
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:56,800
to that mental facility, Emma.

300
00:20:56,933 --> 00:20:59,033
Remember, you hurt me.

301
00:20:59,167 --> 00:21:02,533
You hurt our daughter.
You almost killed Mookie.

302
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:08,667
You hurt her.
I can never forget that.

303
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:09,500
<i> Emma!</i>

304
00:21:09,633 --> 00:21:11,567
<i>You're a monster! I'll kill you!</i>

305
00:21:11,700 --> 00:21:13,233
<i> Mookie!</i>

306
00:21:13,367 --> 00:21:15,367
<i> Emma, let her go!</i>

307
00:21:15,500 --> 00:21:16,733
<i> Demon!</i>

308
00:21:16,867 --> 00:21:18,733
<i> Demon! You're a monster!</i>

309
00:21:18,867 --> 00:21:19,900
<i> I'll kill you!</i>

310
00:21:20,033 --> 00:21:21,200
<i> I'll kill you!</i>

311
00:21:22,300 --> 00:21:24,867
Jade only cared for us, Emma.

312
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:26,867
That's why you were brought
to Havenwood.

313
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:28,833
For you to get better.

314
00:21:28,967 --> 00:21:30,600
But what did you do?

315
00:21:31,567 --> 00:21:32,067
You escaped!

316
00:21:32,933 --> 00:21:38,533
You looked for another man
and forgot about your family!

317
00:21:38,667 --> 00:21:39,700
That's the truth!

318
00:21:40,733 --> 00:21:43,200
Stop accusing me of having
a lover.

319
00:21:43,367 --> 00:21:46,300
And it's not true that I
abandoned you and Mookie.

320
00:21:46,633 --> 00:21:48,633
I wanted to go to you.

321
00:21:48,767 --> 00:21:51,767
But I was scared that Jade would
bring me back to the facility.

322
00:21:51,900 --> 00:21:53,033
That's why I have myself
treated first

323
00:21:53,167 --> 00:21:54,500
and regained my strength.

324
00:21:54,633 --> 00:21:56,867
But now I'm doing well.
I'm getting you back.

325
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:58,067
- You're okay now?
- I'll take you and Mookie back.

326
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,933
Don't touch me, Emma!

327
00:22:00,067 --> 00:22:03,133
You have no one to take back
and no one to come back to.

328
00:22:03,267 --> 00:22:06,500
You better enjoy yourself
with your lover!

329
00:22:06,633 --> 00:22:07,500
Dan.

330
00:22:07,633 --> 00:22:08,700
Dan, wait. Let's talk.

331
00:22:08,833 --> 00:22:09,900
No!

332
00:22:10,033 --> 00:22:14,033
- Dan!
- Danilo!

333
00:22:14,167 --> 00:22:15,567
Dan!

334
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:42,767
I'll help Emma get Mookie back.

335
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:48,400
But I'll make sure that she and
Danilo will never talk again.

336
00:22:49,100 --> 00:22:50,433
Mookie has blocked me.

337
00:22:51,867 --> 00:22:54,500
I should've texted her sooner.

338
00:22:54,633 --> 00:22:57,333
Maybe Jade and Danilo told her
all sorts of things.

339
00:22:57,467 --> 00:23:00,500
Emma's true colors have already
come out.

340
00:23:00,633 --> 00:23:06,100
She can leave you and Mookie
for money.

341
00:23:06,233 --> 00:23:09,500
I'll completely forget her
because of what she did.

342
00:23:09,633 --> 00:23:12,067
And I will never let her
get near my daughter.

343
00:23:17,667 --> 00:23:19,000
Mookie.

344
00:23:19,133 --> 00:23:20,200
Mom?
